headlines.description: — James Wiseman had 18 points and 14 rebounds as the Detroit Pistons ended an 11-game losing streak with a 117-97 win over the Indiana Pacers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiseman's double-double helps Pistons end 11-game skid

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 32 points in his hometown, Kyle Anderson had his third career triple-double and the Minnesota Timberwolves cruised to a 136-115 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Monday night.
— Another night, another close game for Miami.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jimmy Butler scores 24, Heat hold off Jazz 119-115

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 23 points and the Memphis Grizzlies won a second consecutive game against Dallas with all three All-Stars out, beating the Mavericks 104-88 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies beat Mavs again in another meeting sans All-Stars

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 28 points and rookie Jabari Smith Jr. added 24 as the Houston Rockets withstood a late charge to beat the Boston Celtics 111-109 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 28, Rockets outlast Celtics 111-109

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — The Golden State Warriors were tired of losing to the division-rival Suns this season and set their mind on defending against Phoenix just as they did against the talented Bucks last game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors beat Suns 123-112 for 8th straight home victory

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 46 points and 12 rebounds as the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Sacramento Kings 133-124 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis has 46 points, 12 boards as Bucks beat Kings 133-124
